<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,570,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Colouration and Morphology:</emphasis>
Yellowish green in colour (Plate IA). Crown and face with submarginal fuscous lines (Plate IC). Eyes with orange colour (Plate IB). Pronotum yellowish. Scutellum with one longitudinal yellowish fuscous line in middle. Forewings subhyaline and hindwings hyaline. Forewings with black spot at end of clavus. Crown subangularly produced; broadly triangular with a dorsal marginal ridge. Ocelli on margin next to eyes. Genae strongly sinuate below eyes. Pronotum as wide as head, laterally carinate. (Plate IA).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer lobe abruptly narrowed medially, subacute apically, heavily setose in posterior half (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Valve broadly triangular. Subgenital plates elongate, broad basally, tapered apically with 5–6 submarginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[223,314,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Connective “Y”-shaped with small and broad stem, as broad as long (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1217,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); lateral arms wide apart. Style with pointed, claw-shaped apophysis, anterior half with scales; preapical lobe poorly developed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with long dorsal apodeme (curved distally) (
<figureCitation box="[902,996,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft laterally gradually compressed, tapered distad; broader at middle than at apex with pair of identical apical processes (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1424,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1E–F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft not smooth throughout, with pair of apical flares dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[980,1066,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1397,930,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,903,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hecalus erectus sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C. connective, dorsal view; D. subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. aPex of aedeagus; H. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242040/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
