<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="582" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">Remarks:</emphasis>
This new species is very close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1990" authorityName="Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan" authorityYear="1990" box="[698,1134,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghaurii">
<emphasis box="[698,814,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">H. ghaurii</emphasis>
Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan, 
<quantity box="[1078,1134,656,680]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0546" pageId="2" pageNumber="582" unit="in" value="1990.0">1990</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having the pygofer lobe subacute apically and aedeagal shaft broad at middle and tapering at apex. But it differs in having the aedeagal shaft laterally gradually compressed; not smooth dorsally with lateral flares near apex. Style and connective shape are also different from 
<taxonomicName authority="Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1990" authorityName="Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan" authorityYear="1990" box="[408,849,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghaurii">
<emphasis box="[408,525,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="582">H. ghaurii</emphasis>
Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1990
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
